def: Stairs in the back part of a house, as distinguished from thefront stairs; hence, a private or indirect way.
The act of reappointing, or the state of being reappointed.
Any signal giving information about the weather. The systemused by the United States Weather Bureau includes temperature, coldor hot wave, rain or snow, wind direction, storm, and hurricanesignals.
One who speculates in stocks for gain; one whose occupation isto buy and sell stocks. In England a jobber acts as an intermediarybetween brokers.
A trench guarded with a parapet, constructed by besiegers, tosecure themselves and check sallies of the besieged.
Folded together, or upon itself, with the fold runninglengthwise.
An animal having feet that are not apparent.
